{
  "texts": [
    "Note that completion time data for psychoeducation lessons was not collected due to a technical error.",
    "We included the amount of engagement with each of these four features in our statistical models to assess their impact on symptom reduction (GAD-7, PHQ-9, MSQ, and WSAS).",
    "Our analysis revealed that participants who engaged more with the guided sessions showed a significantly greater improvement in anxiety symptoms over time, as measured by GAD-7 scores (guided sessions × week interaction: β = -0.097, p = 0.003; see Fig. 4B).",
    "There was also a trend toward greater improvement in depression symptoms (PHQ-9) for those engaging with guided sessions (guided sessions × week: β = -0.060, p = 0.077).",
    "Additionally, WSAS scores, reflecting general well-being, reduced most for participants who completed guided sessions (guided sessions × week: β = -0.193, p = 0.006)."
  ]
}